<title><![CDATA[5 Morning Rituals for a Calmer, Brighter Day]]></title>
<link>https://example.com/?p=101</link>
<pubDate>Sat, 10 Jan 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=101</guid>
<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>How you spend the first hour of your morning sets the tone for everything that follows. Over the past year I've slowly built a routine that helps me feel grounded before the day even begins.</p>

<p>It started small: a glass of water, ten minutes of stretching, and no phone until I'd had my coffee. Those tiny choices add up to a morning that feels like mine instead of a race against the clock.</p>

<h2>Start with stillness</h2>Before reaching for your to-do list, give yourself five quiet minutes. Light a candle, breathe, and simply notice how you feel. It sounds almost too simple, but it works.

<p>Try one ritual this week and see how it shifts your mood. You might be surprised how much calmer a single small habit can make you feel.</p>]]></content:encoded>
