<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Every spring I do a little closet reset, and every year I'm reminded that a handful of well-chosen pieces beats a closet bursting with options.</p>

<h2>The pieces that earn their place</h2>A crisp white blouse, a pair of tailored linen trousers, and a soft midi dress in a colour that makes you smile. These are the items I rotate again and again.

<p>Accessories do the heavy lifting in spring. A woven bag, delicate gold jewellery, and a pair of comfortable flats can take a simple outfit from plain to polished.</p>

<p>The goal isn't more clothes, it's clothes that work together effortlessly. Build slowly and choose pieces you genuinely love.</p>]]></content:encoded>
