<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=103</guid>
<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>The Amalfi Coast is the kind of place that stays with you long after you've left. Lemon groves, pastel villages, and that impossibly blue water.</p>

<h2>Where to wander</h2>Skip the rush. Spend a morning getting lost in the lanes of Positano, then take the ferry to a quieter village for lunch by the sea.

<p>Eat where the locals eat, order whatever has lemon in it, and don't over-plan. The coast rewards those who slow down.</p>

<p>Two days is just enough to fall in love and start planning your return.</p>]]></content:encoded>
