<title><![CDATA[The Perfect Homemade Berry Smoothie Bowl]]></title>
<link>https://example.com/?p=104</link>
<pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=104</guid>
<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Smoothie bowls are my favourite way to start a warm morning. They feel like a treat but leave me energised for hours.</p>

<h2>The base</h2>Frozen mixed berries, half a banana, a splash of almond milk, and a spoon of yoghurt. Blend until thick enough to eat with a spoon.

<p>Then comes the fun part: granola, fresh fruit, a drizzle of honey, and a sprinkle of seeds. Make it as pretty as you like.</p>

<p>It takes five minutes and never gets boring, because you can change the toppings with the seasons.</p>]]></content:encoded>
