<title><![CDATA[My Everyday Natural Makeup Routine]]></title>
<link>https://example.com/?p=105</link>
<pubDate>Sun, 15 Mar 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=105</guid>
<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My goal with everyday makeup is simple: look like myself, just a little more rested and glowing.</p>

<h2>Skin first</h2>Good skin starts before makeup. A gentle cleanser, a hydrating serum, and SPF every single day make the biggest difference.

<p>For the look itself I keep it light: tinted moisturiser, a touch of cream blush, a swipe of mascara, and a tinted lip balm. Five products, five minutes.</p>

<p>Less really can be more. When your skin feels cared for, you need far less to feel put together.</p>]]></content:encoded>
