<title><![CDATA[Hidden Cafés in Paris Worth Seeking Out]]></title>
<link>https://example.com/?p=108</link>
<pubDate>Sat, 02 May 2026 09:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
<guid isPermaLink="false">https://example.com/?p=108</guid>
<description></description>
<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Paris is full of famous cafés, but the most memorable cups of coffee I've had were in the quiet ones tucked down side streets.</p>

<h2>Off the beaten path</h2>Wander away from the main squares and you'll find tiny spots with mismatched chairs, friendly owners, and pastries still warm from the oven.

<p>Order a café crème, find a seat by the window, and watch the city go by. No rush, no itinerary.</p>

<p>These little places are where Paris feels most like itself.</p>]]></content:encoded>
